1
00:00:00,760 --> 00:00:04,570
♫ It's hard to resist the thing
that I've missed for so long ♫

2
00:00:04,570 --> 00:00:06,380
♫ So long ♫

3
00:00:06,380 --> 00:00:10,200
♫ Can't remember what it's like,
Just remember I need it ♫

4
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:12,620
♫ I need it ♫

5
00:00:12,620 --> 00:00:16,840
♫ You're not what I thought you were ♫

6
00:00:16,840 --> 00:00:18,760
You were ♫

7
00:00:18,760 --> 00:00:22,150
♫ To think I can't find a cure ♫

8
00:00:22,150 --> 00:00:24,720
♫ Find a cure ♫

9
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:30,820
♫ Ooh, you're not what I thought ♫

10
00:00:33,160 --> 00:00:40,400
[If Only You Weren't the One]

11
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:44,570
[Final Episode]

12
00:00:47,770 --> 00:00:49,460
I like you.

13
00:00:57,350 --> 00:00:59,020
Me too.

14
00:01:00,260 --> 00:01:01,980
The second round.

15
00:01:03,460 --> 00:01:06,030
Let's skip out on it.

16
00:01:16,020 --> 00:01:18,040
Wait, wait.

17
00:01:18,885 --> 00:01:20,900
That's too steamy.

18
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:22,910
Let me sit properly.

19
00:01:31,150 --> 00:01:32,650
So?

20
00:01:33,430 --> 00:01:35,020
Well...

21
00:01:39,725 --> 00:01:42,870
Hey! Where are you, phone?

22
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:45,790
Answer me!

23
00:01:46,548 --> 00:01:50,260
Whoa, what are you two doing?

24
00:01:50,260 --> 00:01:51,390
Oh, um...

25
00:01:51,390 --> 00:01:54,980
Oh, so the rumors were true!

26
00:01:54,980 --> 00:01:59,295
- I bet you both are skipping the party!
- No, that's...

27
00:02:03,595 --> 00:02:05,870
What are you talking about?

28
00:02:05,870 --> 00:02:09,985
We came to help you find your phone,
since you were so upset!

29
00:02:09,985 --> 00:02:10,963
He's right.

30
00:02:10,963 --> 00:02:13,730
- Oh, is that it?
- Yeah.

31
00:02:13,730 --> 00:02:16,337
- You guys are so thoughtful.
- Right?

32
00:02:16,337 --> 00:02:18,912
- That's amazing.
- I know, right?

33
00:02:18,912 --> 00:02:21,745
I'll call it now.

34
00:02:21,745 --> 00:02:23,000
I wonder where it is.

35
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,360
Oh, that's a good sign.

36
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,380
- It's over there!
- Here?

37
00:02:28,380 --> 00:02:29,990
Right there!

38
00:02:32,375 --> 00:02:34,650
Ouch...

39
00:02:34,650 --> 00:02:36,730
I sat up for nothing.

40
00:02:36,730 --> 00:02:38,625
So, what happened next?

41
00:02:38,625 --> 00:02:42,729
- Karaoke until morning.
- Yep, that's annoying.

42
00:02:42,729 --> 00:02:46,280
So now Miporin's greeting the new year
feeling frustrated.

43
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:49,230
It's as you say.

44
00:02:50,030 --> 00:02:52,560
Well, that basically means...

45
00:02:53,390 --> 00:02:55,870
it was always Eisei Ureshino.

46
00:03:00,547 --> 00:03:02,190
Huh?
[Eisei Ureshino]

47
00:03:02,190 --> 00:03:04,735
- Whoa!
- Huh?

48
00:03:04,735 --> 00:03:06,745
Pick up! Pick up!

49
00:03:06,745 --> 00:03:09,050
It's fine, you look cute.

50
00:03:09,050 --> 00:03:11,310
I'll be right back.

51
00:03:11,310 --> 00:03:12,680
Huh?

52
00:03:18,775 --> 00:03:20,830
Can't you answer it here?

53
00:03:20,830 --> 00:03:23,400
I already heard everything.

54
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:28,440
Happy New Year.

55
00:03:29,855 --> 00:03:31,940
Happy New Year.

56
00:03:31,940 --> 00:03:33,760
What were you up to just now?

57
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:35,530
Huh? Oh...

58
00:03:35,530 --> 00:03:39,553
You remember Maki-chan? From college.

59
00:03:39,553 --> 00:03:43,180
Oh! Yeah, I remember her.

60
00:03:43,180 --> 00:03:45,785
Kind of vaguely, though.

61
00:03:45,785 --> 00:03:47,960
She's at my place right now.

62
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:51,395
Oh, really? Sounds fun.

63
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:55,600
Why'd you call?

64
00:03:56,250 --> 00:03:59,800
Oh, no, it's nothing really.

65
00:04:00,793 --> 00:04:03,850
Are you going home for the new year?

66
00:04:03,850 --> 00:04:05,450
Huh?

67
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:09,430
No, I'm planning to stay here.

68
00:04:09,430 --> 00:04:12,845
Really? Then let's go somewhere.

69
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:16,750
Huh?

70
00:04:17,535 --> 00:04:19,600
I'm so happy.

71
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:23,660
I thought I wouldn't get to see you
until work started again.

72
00:04:24,535 --> 00:04:27,020
Well, I'll contact you again then.

73
00:04:27,020 --> 00:04:29,430
It's cold, right? Go inside.

74
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:33,780
Hello?

75
00:04:33,780 --> 00:04:36,520
Oh, sorry.

76
00:04:37,230 --> 00:04:39,610
Thanks for calling.

77
00:04:40,830 --> 00:04:43,940
Well, talk to you later.

78
00:04:45,117 --> 00:04:48,447
Well, see you.

79
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,830
Maki-chan!

80
00:05:11,875 --> 00:05:13,970
A happy new year!

81
00:05:13,970 --> 00:05:16,110
Am I right?

82
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:19,790
Yeah!

83
00:05:31,763 --> 00:05:33,163
Hey.

84
00:05:35,955 --> 00:05:37,580
He looks so cool!

85
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:38,980
Hey.

86
00:05:40,855 --> 00:05:44,570
You're cute again this year, Miporin.

87
00:05:44,570 --> 00:05:46,810
Stop joking around.

88
00:05:46,810 --> 00:05:50,855
Alright then, shall we go on our date?

89
00:05:50,855 --> 00:05:52,600
Let's go on our date.

90
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,010
Here.

91
00:06:01,315 --> 00:06:03,730
This reminds me of the company trip.

92
00:06:03,730 --> 00:06:05,380
Yeah, it does.

93
00:06:05,380 --> 00:06:08,650
But back then,
you wouldn't take a bite of my crepe.

94
00:06:08,650 --> 00:06:11,370
You ended up going to a different shop
with Kusaka-kun.

95
00:06:11,370 --> 00:06:15,250
Back then, things felt a bit awkward.

96
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:18,465
I knew it! You actually wanted my food more.

97
00:06:18,465 --> 00:06:20,495
Shut up.

98
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:29,080
Wow, this is so cute.

99
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:31,650
It is.

100
00:06:32,380 --> 00:06:34,820
This would suit you.

101
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:38,260
You think?

102
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:41,760
Want me to buy it?

103
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:43,190
It's okay.

104
00:06:43,190 --> 00:06:45,405
I probably wouldn't wear it much.

105
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:49,335
You could, though! It really suits you.

106
00:06:49,335 --> 00:06:50,680
Nah...

107
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,870
I want to see it.

108
00:06:58,719 --> 00:07:00,079
This one, please.

109
00:07:00,079 --> 00:07:02,529
Thank you very much.

110
00:07:12,860 --> 00:07:14,660
It looks cute.

111
00:07:27,305 --> 00:07:31,640
- Was this on you before?
- Yeah, it was.

112
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,700
Hey.

113
00:07:59,740 --> 00:08:02,170
Do you have a boyfriend?

114
00:08:02,170 --> 00:08:04,685
- Huh?
- Huh?

115
00:08:04,685 --> 00:08:07,180
What kind of question is that?

116
00:08:07,180 --> 00:08:08,680
Huh?

117
00:08:09,555 --> 00:08:12,230
If I said I did, what would you do?

118
00:08:12,230 --> 00:08:16,190
Well, I'd probably be shocked.

119
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:18,860
I don't have one.

120
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:21,200
Of course, I don't.

121
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,190
Oh, good.

122
00:08:23,190 --> 00:08:26,050
Don't ask something so obvious.

123
00:08:26,050 --> 00:08:27,830
Why not?

124
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,970
You could be doing long distance.

125
00:08:29,970 --> 00:08:32,135
Like, "I'm single for now."

126
00:08:32,135 --> 00:08:34,905
Don't lump me in with you.

127
00:08:34,905 --> 00:08:39,520
Huh? Wait, hold on. That's not fair.

128
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,320
I don't have one.

129
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,556
I told you this.

130
00:08:42,556 --> 00:08:46,240
- No, you didn't. We never talked about this.
- No, I did tell you.

131
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:48,815
- No, you didn't.
- I did.

132
00:08:52,410 --> 00:08:54,250
Fine.

133
00:08:58,230 --> 00:09:01,900
I have someone, but not a girlfriend.

134
00:09:06,215 --> 00:09:10,430
- I'm kidding! Don't make that face.
- Stop it.

135
00:09:10,430 --> 00:09:12,025
Come on, Mipo-nyan*!
(*cute nickname referring to a cat's meow)

136
00:09:12,025 --> 00:09:14,160
- Mipo-nyan.
- Hey, stop calling me that!

137
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:15,560
Alright.

138
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:20,760
You're so cute, Miporin.

139
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:25,310
There's no one else.

140
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:30,800
Of course not.

141
00:09:48,590 --> 00:09:50,940
Whoa...

142
00:09:52,125 --> 00:09:54,060
This is so pretty.

143
00:09:54,060 --> 00:09:57,290
I was so curious when I saw the photos.

144
00:10:02,140 --> 00:10:04,870
Whoa, the bathroom's huge.

145
00:10:06,710 --> 00:10:08,570
What's wrong?

146
00:10:09,530 --> 00:10:11,040
Hmm?

147
00:10:11,695 --> 00:10:13,650
Should we order something?

148
00:10:13,650 --> 00:10:16,310
Or we could go out for drinks?

149
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,670
What's wrong?

150
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:24,970
Nothing.

151
00:10:40,143 --> 00:10:42,883
Well? What is it?

152
00:11:05,310 --> 00:11:07,090
Wait.

153
00:11:13,445 --> 00:11:18,150
Before that, we need to talk.

154
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:22,240
Hmm?

155
00:11:30,450 --> 00:11:34,150
What did you mean by "dating"?

156
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:36,800
Huh?

157
00:11:40,626 --> 00:11:43,166
It's just what it sounds like.

158
00:11:52,950 --> 00:11:55,540
So I'd be your girlfriend?

159
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,380
Isn't that obvious?

160
00:12:05,770 --> 00:12:08,730
Can I trust you?

161
00:12:08,730 --> 00:12:10,230
Huh?

162
00:12:14,050 --> 00:12:15,910
Oh...

163
00:12:25,470 --> 00:12:27,270
Why not?

164
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:46,550
Of course.

165
00:12:54,930 --> 00:12:58,640
Why would I ask that after all this?

166
00:13:02,330 --> 00:13:03,730
Huh?

167
00:13:12,410 --> 00:13:16,690
After all, we're accomplices.

168
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:24,160
But...

169
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,970
I did like you.

170
00:13:46,385 --> 00:13:51,720
My encounter with this guy
came at the right time.

171
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:57,875
Things with my boyfriend of six years
had gone stale.

172
00:13:57,875 --> 00:14:01,966
My friend, who'd just fallen in love,
seemed so radiant.

173
00:14:01,966 --> 00:14:06,376
So I went to a group date as a stand-in,
even though it's out of character.

174
00:14:08,270 --> 00:14:09,670
Ah.

175
00:14:13,590 --> 00:14:15,180
Sorry.

176
00:14:16,650 --> 00:14:18,720
Let me hear more.

177
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:25,970
🚩 Channel Managers 🚩
shraddhasingh & lilgr84_544

178
00:14:25,970 --> 00:14:30,970
🚩 Chief Segmenter 🚩
a_hauth_238

179
00:14:30,970 --> 00:14:35,950
🚩 Chief Editor 🚩
trangstar888

180
00:14:35,950 --> 00:14:40,960
🚩 Translation Editor 🚩
xylune

181
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:45,970
🚩 Special thanks to our language moderators and their teams 🚩

182
00:14:48,322 --> 00:14:53,220
I knew it was wrong, but I couldn't resist.

183
00:15:15,535 --> 00:15:17,110
What?

184
00:15:17,110 --> 00:15:19,230
Why are you avoiding me?

185
00:15:19,230 --> 00:15:21,820
Well, because...

186
00:15:25,380 --> 00:15:28,190
You're so serious, Miho-chan.

187
00:15:28,190 --> 00:15:30,260
Stop it.

188
00:15:34,530 --> 00:15:36,460
Do you regret it?

189
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:42,500
Of course I do.

190
00:16:10,005 --> 00:16:15,320
If it were just once,
I could've written it off as an accident.

191
00:16:16,140 --> 00:16:18,010
And yet...

192
00:16:21,770 --> 00:16:23,440
No.

193
00:16:24,510 --> 00:16:26,610
I know it's wrong, but...

194
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:48,500
Miporin, you're so cute.

195
00:16:49,915 --> 00:16:55,180
When I'm with this guy,
love becomes confusing.

196
00:16:59,535 --> 00:17:05,320
Pleasure courses through my entire body,
overriding the guilt.

197
00:17:07,790 --> 00:17:09,720
I like you...

198
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:13,460
I like you.

199
00:17:22,810 --> 00:17:25,970
We should stop seeing each other.

200
00:17:30,510 --> 00:17:32,780
You mean he found out?

201
00:17:34,747 --> 00:17:36,347
I think so.

202
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:41,300
So let's stop now.

203
00:17:53,530 --> 00:17:55,470
I see.

204
00:17:59,740 --> 00:18:01,380
Okay.

205
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,180
You're right.

206
00:18:17,970 --> 00:18:19,470
So?

207
00:18:22,340 --> 00:18:24,630
What is it that you want?

208
00:18:26,420 --> 00:18:27,900
Huh?

209
00:18:30,095 --> 00:18:32,050
I told you.

210
00:18:32,050 --> 00:18:33,910
What do you want to do?

211
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,920
What about you?

212
00:18:50,890 --> 00:18:52,670
I...

213
00:18:56,580 --> 00:18:59,030
will do whatever you want.

214
00:19:02,730 --> 00:19:04,670
That's not fair.

215
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:18,580
This is the last time.

216
00:19:34,930 --> 00:19:36,770
This is...

217
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:43,700
the last time.

218
00:19:53,210 --> 00:19:54,990
One last time.

219
00:20:02,300 --> 00:20:07,220
This feeling, this kiss...

220
00:20:09,890 --> 00:20:13,750
It'll all end after this.

221
00:20:16,583 --> 00:20:24,047
Although I really wanted
for this to last forever, with Eisei...

222
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:47,050
♫ We walked through the city at daybreak,
soaked by the rain ♫

223
00:20:47,050 --> 00:20:51,880
♫ You and me in the rain ♫

224
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:56,030
♫ Rather than trusting others ♫

225
00:20:57,080 --> 00:20:58,610
Hey.

226
00:20:59,570 --> 00:21:01,380
What did you mean earlier?

227
00:21:01,380 --> 00:21:05,560
♫ I kept looking at you ♫

228
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,897
What did I mean?

229
00:21:09,990 --> 00:21:13,140
It's just what it sounds like.

230
00:21:13,140 --> 00:21:16,670
♫ Don't let go... ♫

231
00:21:16,670 --> 00:21:19,860
♫ Of my hand ♫

232
00:21:19,860 --> 00:21:22,780
You want to date after all this?

233
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,380
That'd be such a waste.

234
00:21:30,350 --> 00:21:35,770
♫ Need to think about tomorrow ♫

235
00:21:43,900 --> 00:21:49,280
After all, this is the kind of relationship
we have, isn't it?

236
00:22:01,470 --> 00:22:08,130
[If Only You Weren't the One]

237
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:12,880
♫ Bathed in acacia tones ♫

238
00:22:14,001 --> 00:22:16,760
- Have a good day.
- You too.

239
00:22:18,138 --> 00:22:22,050
You and Kusaka-san would make a great couple.

240
00:22:22,050 --> 00:22:23,260
You're not going to date?

241
00:22:23,260 --> 00:22:25,230
What? I told you before

242
00:22:25,230 --> 00:22:27,595
that I'm not in the right mindset right now.

243
00:22:27,595 --> 00:22:30,005
Oh?

244
00:22:30,005 --> 00:22:31,970
Oh, how's your new place?

245
00:22:31,970 --> 00:22:34,830
Yeah, it's comfortable. A nice, quiet place.

246
00:22:34,830 --> 00:22:37,540
Oh, that's good to hear.

247
00:22:37,540 --> 00:22:41,150
But you had your last place
for ten years after college, right?

248
00:22:41,150 --> 00:22:42,590
Why now?

249
00:22:42,590 --> 00:22:45,540
Well, I needed a change.

250
00:22:45,540 --> 00:22:47,570
And to start fresh.

251
00:22:47,570 --> 00:22:49,040
I see.

252
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:51,045
Well, I'm glad you like it.

253
00:22:51,045 --> 00:22:53,355
Yeah.

254
00:22:53,355 --> 00:22:56,080
Oh, I forgot I have a client call.

255
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:57,505
Mihono-san, please go ahead.

256
00:22:57,505 --> 00:22:59,420
Okay. Thanks for your hard work.

257
00:22:59,420 --> 00:23:05,130
♫ Need to think about tomorrow ♫

258
00:23:10,790 --> 00:23:16,800
🚩 Thank you for watching 🚩
"If Only You Weren't the One"

259
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:44,960
[This drama is fiction.]
